J. Moustakas
2005 Nov 18, U of A

Construct a Pegase grid according to a range of star-formation
histories and metallicities.  Assume a Salpeter IMF throughout. 

Note: removed "0" from ages.dat.

##########################
Construct the SSPs
##########################

First construct the SSPs for the Salpeter IMF (0.1-100) and the
default stellar evolutionary parameters.

##########################
Infall models
##########################

The following describes the file called "infall_salp_scenarios.input".
For simplicity I only describe the first metallicity.

infall_salp_scenarios.output             # scenarios.f output file name
infall_salp_SSPs.dat                     # SSPs pre-computed by SSPs.f
0.05                                     # default binary fraction
infall_salp_eta1.0_tinfall1.0_tau4.0.dat # spectra.f output file name
0.0                                      # metallicity of the ISM at t=0
y                                        # infall - yes
1000.0                                   # infall time scale [Myr]
0.0                                      # metallicity of the infalling gas
10                                       # star formation scenario [defined in spectra.f]
2                                        # number of free parameters in the SFR law
4000.0                                   # characteristic time for star formation [tau or p1]
1.0                                      # star formation efficiency factor [p2]
y                                        # consistent evolution of the stellar metallicity
0.0                                      # mass fraction of substellar objects formed
n                                        # no galactic winds
y                                        # include nebular emission
2                                        # inclination-averaged extinction for a disk geometry
.
.
.
end

% /bin/rm infall_salp_scenarios.output ; ./scenarios < infall_salp_scenarios.input
% /bin/rm infall_salp_eta?.?_tinfall?.?_tau?.?.dat ; echo "infall_salp_scenarios.output" | ./spectra
